# Phase Gate Rule

## The Rule

Code must only implement what is scoped to the **current active phase**.

The current phase is tracked in [MANIFEST.md](../../MANIFEST.md#11-development-phases--roadmap) — look for the phase with status "In Progress".

## Phase Component Ownership

Use these tables to determine which phase owns a given piece of work:

### Components by Phase

**Phase 1 (Foundation):**
- Engine: HTTP server, WebSocket, lifecycle, file watcher
- Component handle system: `ComponentHandle`, `InputHandle`, registry, ID generation
- HTML renderer: component → HTML string; `FRAGMENT` send logic
- Client: WebSocket manager + `outerHTML` swap (no diffing library)
- CSS foundation: `lastriko.css` tokens + base styles, theme switching
- Plugin interface: types only, stubs
- CLI scaffold: create-lastriko

**Phase 2 (MVP Components):**
- `button`, `textInput`, `numberInput`, `slider`, `toggle`, `select`, `fileUpload`
- `text`, `markdown`, `image`, `imageGrid`, `code`, `json`, `table`, `metric`, `progress`
- `shell`, `grid`, `tabs`, `card`, `divider`, `spacer`
- `toast`, `alert`, `loading`, `streamText`
- `chatUI`, `promptEditor`
- Complete theme (all tokens, toolbar toggle)
- Node.js 22+ support (alongside Bun)
- npm publish: lastriko v0.1.0

**Phase 3 (Advanced):**
- `multiSelect`, `colorPicker`, `dateInput`
- `video`, `audio`, `diff`
- `accordion`, `fullscreen`
- `modelCompare`, `parameterPanel`, `filmStrip`, `beforeAfter`
- WebSocket message batching
- Virtual scrolling in `table`
- Accessibility audit
- Multi-page support (`ui.page()`, `ui.navigate()`)
- Improved hot reload (scroll/state preservation)
- Error boundaries

**Phase 4 (Plugins):**
- `@lastriko/plugin-openai`
- `@lastriko/plugin-anthropic`
- `@lastriko/plugin-ollama`
- `@lastriko/plugin-neutralino` (stub → full)
- `@lastriko/plugin-auth`
- Full `PluginContext` implementation (all methods)

**Phase 5 (Distribution):**
- `bunx lastriko export --desktop`
- `bunx lastriko export --static`
- `bunx lastriko export --docker`
- `bunx lastriko share`
- `@lastriko/plugin-static`

**Phase 6 (Ecosystem):**
- Templates gallery
- Community plugin scaffolding
- Community plugin scaffolding and templates gallery
- Note: huggingface/replicate/generic-llm are Phase 4–5 stretch goals, not Phase 6

## Violation Examples

These are phase gate violations — do not do them:

```typescript
// ❌ Adding accordion in Phase 2 (it's a Phase 3 component)
ui.accordion([{ label: 'Advanced', content: ... }]);

// ❌ Implementing desktop export in Phase 3
const neutralino = await import('@neutralinojs/neutralino');

// ❌ Writing OpenAI plugin code in Phase 1
class OpenAIPlugin implements LastrikoPlugin { ... }
```

## When You See Phase-Gated Items

If you encounter a request to implement a component or feature that belongs to a later phase:

1. Check: is the current phase actually that later phase? (Look at MANIFEST.md)
2. If yes: proceed, make sure the manifesto has the spec before coding
3. If no: decline to implement it, explain which phase it belongs to

## Advancing Phases

Phases advance when their exit criteria are met. **Do not advance a phase until ALL exit criteria pass.** Exit criteria are defined in [MANIFEST.md](../../MANIFEST.md#11-development-phases--roadmap) (roadmap + §11.1 foundation summary) and in each remaining phase document:

- [PHASE-3.md](../../docs/phases/PHASE-3.md#exit-criteria)
- [PHASE-4.md](../../docs/phases/PHASE-4.md#exit-criteria)
- [PHASE-5.md](../../docs/phases/PHASE-5.md#exit-criteria)
- [PHASE-6.md](../../docs/phases/PHASE-6.md#exit-criteria)

When a phase is complete, update MANIFEST.md to mark it as "Complete" and the next phase as "In Progress".
